Goblins in the God Wars Dungeon are troops for the Bandosian army from the goblin tribe Rekeshuun, fighting against the other monsters inside the dungeon. They are considerably stronger than most goblins found elsewhere and can be killed for killcount.

Drops[edit | edit source]

Drop rates estimated based on 1,024 samples from the Drop Log Project, unless otherwise cited.

These goblins are all level 84, and can be found in the northwest (Bandos) corner of the centre area. They are not found in Bandos' encampment. They are weak against earth spells.

Update history[edit | edit source]

This information has been compiled as part of the update history project. Some updates may not be included – see here for how to help out!
  • patch 19 December 2012 (Update):
    • Several goblins have been graphically updated to the same standard as the recently reworked goblins.
  • patch 13 May 2010 (Update):
    • Goblin death animations should now be a bit quicker.
  • update 28 August 2007 (Update):
    • Added to game.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • Prior to the Evolution of Combat, the goblins carrying banners were never aggressive and would run from players when approached. As a result of this, it contradicted their examine text, which was "A soldier to the death." These goblins also had much lower hitpoints than the other goblins in the dungeon, only having 3 hitpoints.
